OL,3,CWater bills to rise by an average of
OL,4,C#31 a year over next five years
OL,6,FDespite the average #31 a year
OL,7,Fincrease figure, households will face
OL,8,Fa heavy average hike of #86 or 20% in
OL,9,Fthe next year, excluding inflation,
OL,10,Ffollowed by smaller increases over the
OL,11,Fnext four years.
OL,13,FThe average bill will rise by a total
OL,14,Fof #157 or 36% in the next five years.
OL,16,FSome water companies have been allowed
OL,17,Fto increase prices significantly.
OL,18,FSouthern Water customers will face a
OL,19,F53% increase and Severn Trent
OL,20,Fhouseholds will see their bills rise
OL,21,Fby 47%, before inflation.
