OL,3,CWater bills to rise by an average of
OL,4,C#31 a year over next five years
OL,6,FMike Keil, chief executive of the
OL,7,FConsumer Council for Water (CCW),
OL,8,Fcalled for a social tariff and better
OL,9,Fsupport for Brits who will bear the
OL,10,Ffinancial brunt of the increase in
OL,11,Fbills.
OL,13,F"These bill rises may be less than
OL,14,Fwhat water companies wanted but they
OL,15,Fare still more than what many people
OL,16,Fcan afford," explained.
OL,18,F"Customers will be hit particularly
OL,19,Fhard from April, with a large chunk of
OL,20,Fthese increases frontloaded into next
OL,21,Fyear ` on top of inflation.
